# Mobile-first design

- Write base styles for the smallest screens first; avoid “desktop-first” overrides.
- Prefer `@media (min-width: ...)` breakpoints so each query scales up from mobile.
- Use flexible layouts by default: `flex`/`grid` + wrapping (`flex-wrap: wrap`, `gap`, `max-width: 100%`).
- Avoid fixed widths/heights where possible; use `min-height`/`max-width` and fluid spacing in `rem`.
- Ensure tap targets meet accessibility expectations (aim for ~44px min height/width) and keep interactive elements comfortably spaced.
- Make typography responsive (prefer `clamp()` for font sizes/line-heights).

## Example (CSS)

```css
.card {
  padding: 0.75rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.5rem;
}

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .card {
    flex-direction: row;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
  }
}
```
